  "description": [
    "EDUCATION IN THE SOVIET UNION Emphasis on Sciences and Math Running Ahead of American Pace By DR GEORGE V KIRK I j Last week we discussed the typical Soviet tenyear curricu lum including all subjects which the Soviet student will take while in school and gave emdent phasis to the special program for languages that exist in the Soviet schools Before we get into the area of this weeks J emphasis that is Science and Math of the Soviet school we will consider some of the com parisons between the Soviet and American systems In the first four grades the Soviet and American systems are quite alike American schools do stress more social studies or history in grades 1 2 and 3 than the Soviet schools never theless the great emphasis in both schools is language liter EDITORS NOTE This is the third in a series of ar ticles written especially for this paper by Dr Kirk su perintendent of Smyrna Special Schools on his re cent trip to the Soviet Un ion Questions addressed to the author concerning the trip people living condi tions etc behind the Iron Curtain may be sent to The Smyrna Times Kirk Pro pect"
